The paper deals with the problem of efficiently learning mixture of Gaussians, which is a fundamental problem in statistics and learning theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of tools for bounding smallest singular values of structured random matrices, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The algorithmic ideas involve decomposing the moment tensor of the Gaussian mixture by exploiting its structural properties, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the combinatorial structure of higher order moments of Gaussian distributions, which could be related to cs.ST (Statistics Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
